  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/picture_story/\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dca-\u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2-\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dab\u0da7-\u0dba\u0daf\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd3-PMB\u0dba\u0dda-\u0dbb\u0dd4--\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2-\u0d9c\u0dab\u0db1\u0d9a-\u0dc0\u0dd3-\u0db8\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca\u0db4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3-\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2---\u0d9a\u0dd8\u0dc2\u0dd2-\u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dda-\u0d85\u0dc0\u0db0\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7/10-396887",
  "time_ut": 1662349708,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dab\u0da7 \u0dba\u0daf\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd3 PMB\u0dba\u0dda \u0dbb\u0dd4. \u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 \u0d9c\u0dab\u0db1\u0d9a \u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0db8\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca\u0db4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2 - \u0d9a\u0dd8\u0dc2\u0dd2 \u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d85\u0dc0\u0db0\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "While rice was burning, PMB's Rs. Lakhs of paddy is rotting in Manampitiya - Agriculture Minister's attention",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Farmers and representatives of farmers' organizations in the area say that a large stock of rice bought from farmers in the 2015 spring season is rotting and being destroyed in a paddy warehouse in Aralagangwila, Polonnaruwa, which belongs to the Paddy Marketing Board.",
        "Farmers allege that rice has been purchased from the rice marketing board only once in one of the two warehouses of the Aralagangwila paddy marketing board built at a cost of 100 lakh rupees.",
        "The former secretary of the business committee of Mahaweli B zone said that the seats of the roofs of the storage complex were damaged and broken, and hundreds of thousands of kilos of paddy had rotted and destroyed due to the water that fell in during the rainy season. Mr. Sarath Rajapaksa mentioned.",
        "Mr. Sarath Rajapaksa added that one of the warehouses has been damaged by wild elephants and vandals have tried to remove the plates from the warehouse, and he has requested the relevant authorities to save this national resource and prepare the warehouses to buy rice from the farmers of Mahaweli B Zone, Vijayabapura Division this year. said.",
        "If these two warehouse complexes worth 100 lakhs built by the government at the expense of public money are not utilized, then some other industry should be started.",
        "The representatives of farmers' organizations in Mahaweli B region also called for the immediate attention of the minister and to start a program to take advantage of it.",
        "When we asked Mr. Nimal Ekanayake, the Polonnaru District Manager of the Paddy Marketing Board, about these two decaying paddy storage complexes and the decomposing paddy stock, he said that the storage complex is in the custody of the Ampara Manager of the Paddy Marketing Board.",
        "Accordingly, in a telephone inquiry with Mr. Shanta Kumara, the Ampara District Manager of the Rice Marketing Board, he mentioned that it is a stock of waste rice that is rotting in this way. Mr. Shanta Kumara said that those removed from the wheat bags are in M's warehouse, and the waste wheat should be given through a committee during the release. Mr. Shanta Kumara also said that due to lack of service in the Polonnaruwa district of the Marketing Board, Ampara employees were used to purchase rice from Aralagangwila rice warehouse in one season.",
        "Mr. Shanta Kumara also said that as soon as the money is received from the Paddy Marketing Board, the Polonnaruwa offices will buy the farmers' paddy crops for the warehouse."
      ],
